[
    {
        "content": "<p>what if instead of having <code>|</code> separate different alternatives in pattern matches, we used <code>or</code>?</p>\n<p>e.g.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">str</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">str</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">FileErr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">BadUtf8</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"err\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 497298032,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738535721
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>seems more self-descriptive</p>",
        "id": 497298146,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738535811
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It is more self-descriptive, but the value of symbols here are that they're more visually sparse and distinct than words. I think the pipe is better at chunking patterns for the eyes</p>",
        "id": 497298956,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738536407
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Though <code>or</code> would make parsing simpler/more performant, the parser is probably so cheap compared to the rest of the compiler that I don't think a minor readability loss is worth it</p>",
        "id": 497298992,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738536457
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If everyone else thinks it's more readable, then sure. That's separate, though</p>",
        "id": 497299010,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738536479
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah that's why I didn't bring up the parsing considerations here - I'm curious what others think just in terms of how the code reads!</p>",
        "id": 497299097,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738536534
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Really depends on the syntax highlighting</p>",
        "id": 497299132,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738536570
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If it’s good, I think it reads fine</p>",
        "id": 497299139,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738536583
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>let's assume it's good <span aria-label=\"big smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"big smile\">:big_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 497299151,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738536595
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Though this style you’ve put here is unusual</p>",
        "id": 497299213,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738536614
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>An or pattern in the interior of another pattern that is</p>",
        "id": 497299228,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738536633
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah I don't think we actually support it yet <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 497299269,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738536659
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I’d expect to see:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">str</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">str</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">FileErr</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">BadUtf8</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"err\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 497299307,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738536697
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Are you including that in this proposal?</p>",
        "id": 497299362,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738536730
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe there is a benefit to having a different syntax for \"Types\" <code>|</code> as opposed to \"values\" <code>or</code>.</p>\n<p>Personally I think the <code>or</code> is objectively clearer and more expressive of intent.</p>",
        "id": 497299391,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1738536762
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>IE, making alternatives inside of a pattern legal?</p>",
        "id": 497299400,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738536770
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think we should absolutely allow that</p>",
        "id": 497299416,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738536795
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's very useful at removing clutter from complex patterns</p>",
        "id": 497299424,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738536810
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don’t know if I’ve seen that in a language</p>",
        "id": 497299425,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738536811
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But seems useful</p>",
        "id": 497299428,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738536818
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tag_union</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Apples</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"delicious\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Bananas</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Oranges</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"gross\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tag_union</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Apples</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"delicious\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Bananas</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Oranges</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"gross\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 497299498,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1738536853
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Makes me want to suggest:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tag_union</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Apples</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">then</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"delicious\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Bananas</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Oranges</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">then</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"gross\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 497299622,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738536964
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Rust does it</p>",
        "id": 497299649,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738536993
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>wait we all know that Roc already supports <code>|</code> like this today, right?</p>",
        "id": 497299664,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738537009
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm just talking about renaming it to <code>or</code></p>",
        "id": 497299679,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738537022
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It supports it inside of a destructure?</p>",
        "id": 497299701,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738537054
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm talking with Anthony about | within a pattern</p>",
        "id": 497299704,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738537057
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Like Rust does</p>",
        "id": 497299712,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738537063
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don’t think I’ve ever seen that in Rust either, but I trust Sam on that</p>",
        "id": 497299917,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738537214
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think it's fine with syntax highlighting</p>",
        "id": 497300072,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738537334
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You’d definitely want different formatting I think for multiline</p>",
        "id": 497300242,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738537468
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Trailing <code>or</code> instead of leading with <code>|</code></p>",
        "id": 497300285,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738537506
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I still have no good heuristic for when we use symbols instead of keywords. It feels like we do it for</p>\n<ul>\n<li>words are unwieldy, e.g. &gt;= vs <code>gte</code></li>\n<li>we use it a lot, so we want to make it terse</li>\n<li>control flow, e.g. we're taking a when branch</li>\n<li>we want to chunk visual sections</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 497300345,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738537560
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tag_union</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Apples</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"delicious\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Bananas</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Oranges</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"gross\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 497300347,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738537562
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I really don't like that you need to read the end of a line to scan the code</p>",
        "id": 497300408,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738537592
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Not a fan of <code>or</code> if that's required</p>",
        "id": 497300418,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738537604
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Wow, really?</p>",
        "id": 497300430,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738537618
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Not perfect either, but we can use two spaces before the <code>or</code> to keep it at the start of the line</p>",
        "id": 497300463,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738537642
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This reads better to you?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tag_union</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Apples</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"delicious\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Bananas</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Oranges</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"gross\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 497300472,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738537653
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I've been trying to push for scanability</p>",
        "id": 497300482,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738537670
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That’s what the trailing or was for</p>",
        "id": 497300537,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738537685
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I figured with syntax highlighting it’s distinct</p>",
        "id": 497300543,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738537698
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And I think we either need an obvious symbol like | or some indent</p>",
        "id": 497300544,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738537699
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tag_union</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Apples</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"delicious\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Bananas</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Oranges</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"gross\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 497300554,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738537722
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I want to really narrowly scope what I'm talking about in this thread</p>",
        "id": 497300559,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738537728
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it's just find/replace <code>|</code> with <code>or</code>, that's it <span aria-label=\"big smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"big smile\">:big_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 497300582,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738537747
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>everything else is out of scope for this idea</p>",
        "id": 497300592,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738537757
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I agree</p>",
        "id": 497300596,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738537760
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sure</p>",
        "id": 497300603,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738537768
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But how we format code with or affects my decision</p>",
        "id": 497300617,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738537779
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Then this is what you get on multiline:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tag_union</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Apples</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"delicious\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Bananas</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Oranges</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"gross\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 497300624,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738537787
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And I think that influences opinions</p>",
        "id": 497300640,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738537798
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Because as Anthony is pointing out, the readability is worse for multiline</p>",
        "id": 497300641,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738537800
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If we couldn't change formatting, I'd say it's not worth it</p>",
        "id": 497300696,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738537812
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Even if we could, I'm not sure</p>",
        "id": 497300704,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738537819
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Without the real syntax highlighting it might be hard to gauge fairly</p>",
        "id": 497300746,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738537861
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In Ruby or is an operator not a keyword</p>",
        "id": 497300775,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738537887
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If when, is, and or were highlighted the same it might strike you differently</p>",
        "id": 497300844,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738537923
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>what does the ideal <code>or</code> formatting look like next to the ideal <code>|</code> formatting?</p>",
        "id": 497305586,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738541354
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(I'm on mobile, can't write them out easily <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span>)</p>",
        "id": 497305604,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738541369
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well I thought this <a href=\"#narrow/channel/304641-ideas/topic/.60or.60.20instead.20of.20.60.7C.60.20in.20.60when.60.20branches/near/497299498\">#ideas &gt; &#96;or&#96; instead of &#96;|&#96; in &#96;when&#96; branches @ 💬</a> for single line</p>",
        "id": 497305685,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1738541409
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or this for multi-line</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tag_union</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Apples</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"s2\">\"delicious\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Bananas</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Oranges</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"s2\">\"gross\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tag_union</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Apples</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"s2\">\"delicious\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Bananas</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Oranges</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"s2\">\"gross\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>edit : updated based on Sam's comment below</p>",
        "id": 497305764,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1738541466
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think the newlines are doing work here</p>",
        "id": 497305943,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738541578
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If the patterns are longer for the <code>or</code> example, it's a bigger problem that <code>or</code> is at the end</p>",
        "id": 497305997,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738541615
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Updated it to have leading <code>or</code> to help with longer patterns</p>",
        "id": 497306102,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1738541692
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>To my eyes, the trailing or still reads better</p>",
        "id": 497306128,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738541711
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But I am but one man</p>",
        "id": 497306160,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738541733
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"781658\">Anthony Bullard</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/304641-ideas/topic/.60or.60.20instead.20of.20.60.7C.60.20in.20.60when.60.20branches/near/497306128\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>To my eyes, the trailing or still reads better</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Here you go</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tag_union</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Apples</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"s2\">\"delicious\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Bananas</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Oranges</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"s2\">\"gross\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 497306284,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1738541835
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I like the trailing <code>or</code>. I'm definitely more familiar with the <code>|</code>. </p>\n<p>I do think the <code>or</code>'s are clearer for someone who isn't already steeped in programming language syntax. It almost reads like a sentence.</p>",
        "id": 497306381,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1738541895
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it feels to me like the tradeoffs  between <code>or</code> and <code>|</code> are similar to the tradeoffs between <code>or</code> and <code>||</code> in terms of readability</p>",
        "id": 497306541,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738542025
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"515757\">Luke Boswell</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/304641-ideas/topic/.60or.60.20instead.20of.20.60.7C.60.20in.20.60when.60.20branches/near/497306381\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I like the trailing <code>or</code>. I'm definitely more familiar with the <code>|</code>. </p>\n<p>I do think the <code>or</code>'s are clearer for someone who isn't already steeped in programming language syntax. It almost reads like a sentence.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This is why I have-jokingly suggested that if this moved forward, replacing <code>-&gt;</code> with <code>then</code> makes sense as well.  But there are lots of opinions on words over symbols here</p>",
        "id": 497306919,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738542357
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I personally like <code>then</code> over <code>-&gt;</code> in the abstract</p>",
        "id": 497308066,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738543218
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it wasn't well-received last time but I also don't think we really seriously considered it haha</p>",
        "id": 497308092,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738543238
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(the thing I like about it in the abstract is just that <code>-&gt;</code> now means \"pure function\" and <code>when</code> branches are purity-agnostic)</p>",
        "id": 497308138,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738543271
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yep</p>",
        "id": 497308435,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738543494
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I like <code>then</code> also... in general I think the keywords are clearer.</p>",
        "id": 497308603,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1738543637
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Especially with control flow</p>",
        "id": 497308642,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1738543670
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>if anyone wants to start a thread about it, feel free!</p>",
        "id": 497309057,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738543957
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I really dislike <code>or</code> in when branches, just feels verbose and overly wordy....but I am used to rust which just uses a <code>|</code>. I like <code>or</code> for booleans. I'm not a fan of it for patterns.</p>",
        "id": 497312455,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1738546724
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But I'm sure I would eventually get used to whatever</p>",
        "id": 497312470,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1738546739
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah I also much prefer pipe here</p>",
        "id": 497315979,
        "sender_full_name": "Isaac Van Doren",
        "timestamp": 1738549179
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I like <code>or</code>. I feel like it unifies the syntax with <code>ifs</code>. It seems inconsistent to have different operators when you're \"matching\" on boolean expressions vs matching on types. It would be nice to be able to read <code>ifs</code> and <code>whens</code> in the same way and that could be another argument for adding <code>then</code> too</p>",
        "id": 497325094,
        "sender_full_name": "Ben",
        "timestamp": 1738555862
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I mean they functionally do different things</p>",
        "id": 497325211,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1738555956
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>One is selecting from many possible patterns. The other passing on the first true value found with short circuiting.</p>",
        "id": 497325272,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1738556025
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Just to push a bit - <code>if</code> can be thought of as matching when you're interested in one possible pattern. <code>when</code> pattern matching can short circuit as well.</p>",
        "id": 497325575,
        "sender_full_name": "Ben",
        "timestamp": 1738556240
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There is nothing to short circuit cause there are no evaluated expressions</p>",
        "id": 497325667,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1738556298
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"343810\">Brendan Hansknecht</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/304641-ideas/topic/.60or.60.20instead.20of.20.60.7C.60.20in.20.60when.60.20branches/near/497325667\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>There is nothing to short circuit cause there are no evaluated expressions</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>You're right, I take that back</p>",
        "id": 497325717,
        "sender_full_name": "Ben",
        "timestamp": 1738556341
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But yeah, I do agree that they still roughly are the same idea, so it may feel nice for consistency.</p>",
        "id": 497325752,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1738556383
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tag_union</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Apples</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"delicious\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Bananas</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Oranges</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">or</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"s2\">\"gross\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This is what I think will get hairy. We can force the formatter to move single line branches to be multiline if any patterns are multiline? Not great, but I think it'd be better than the above</p>",
        "id": 497340074,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1738564027
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or is very familiar in expressions, but seeing it in a pattern match makes me feel like it's doing some sort of calculation or transformation of the types, but it's really more like control flow here. Like, <code>Err(FileErr or BadUtf8) -&gt;</code> makes me think you're creating some new type/value/concept <code>FileErr or BadUtf8</code>, and it makes me want to do something like</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>pattern myPattern = FileErr or BadUtf8\n...\nErr(myPattern) -&gt;\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>By contrast <code>|</code> feels more like it's part of the control flow and the syntax of <code>when</code>, just like <code>,</code> is part of the syntax of lists, and I don't have the same urge to see it as a calculation or pull it into a variable.</p>",
        "id": 497494612,
        "sender_full_name": "Sky Rose",
        "timestamp": 1738603656
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>seems like there isn't enough interest to justify changing, so let's keep it as <code>|</code></p>",
        "id": 497538364,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1738619354
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"607308\">Sky Rose</span> has marked this topic as resolved.</p>",
        "id": 497538999,
        "sender_full_name": "Notification Bot",
        "timestamp": 1738619589
    }
